they're very focused.
Okay, I gotta go.

18:58.360 --> 19:00.828
Look, give me Jake's phone.

19:00.830 --> 19:03.822
I'll get rid of it for you.
No, i-i can't ask you
to do that.

19:03.840 --> 19:08.106
I want to. It's one less
miserable thing for you
to deal with today.

19:08.110 --> 19:10.761
Plus, I'll do it
better than you.

19:19.720 --> 19:21.483
Emma duval!

19:22.720 --> 19:26.451
(Students whispering)

19:29.060 --> 19:31.949
I hear you have something
you want to show me.

19:46.410 --> 19:48.105
Follow us, please.

19:56.820 --> 20:00.483
You ratted her out.
Shut up.

20:18.180 --> 20:20.330
Kieran made it back.

20:20.350 --> 20:23.979
But not happily.
(Ringtone playing)

20:24.450 --> 20:27.146
Hey! What happened to you?

20:27.950 --> 20:30.487
We failed,
they took Kieran away,
and now they're taking Emma,

20:30.490 --> 20:32.549
and I ended up trapped
out in the halls.

20:32.560 --> 20:34.255
Kieran's back,
but he doesn't look

20:34.260 --> 20:36.125
like he wants to chat,
so who knows?

20:36.130 --> 20:37.427
This Is so screwed up.

20:37.430 --> 20:40.354
Somebody planted
Jake's phone in Emma's bag.

20:40.370 --> 20:42.065
Wait, what? That's why
they're taking her?

20:42.070 --> 20:48.202
I don't know,
but they walked her out of here
like some sort of criminal.

20:48.540 --> 20:52.203
I'm starting to think the person
that they should be questioning

20:52.210 --> 20:53.438
is sitting right here.

20:53.450 --> 20:55.372
Who are you talking about?

21:01.020 --> 21:05.354
So, you have no idea
how that phone wound up
in your backpack?

21:05.360 --> 21:07.851
No, but whoever
put it in there

21:07.860 --> 21:10.522
is probably the same person
who attacked me last night

21:10.530 --> 21:13.397
and probably the same person
who killed Jake.

21:13.400 --> 21:16.528
So, you believe
that you're being targeted
just like before?

21:16.540 --> 21:18.997
Yes.
You, um...

21:19.000 --> 21:21.264
Went away for a while
for treatment. PTSD.

21:21.270 --> 21:26.879
Yeah, I had some stress issues
that I had to deal with after...

21:26.880 --> 21:30.145
After what happened
on the dock. Huh.

21:30.150 --> 21:32.118
And you were admitted
to the psych ward

21:32.120 --> 21:35.908
after witnessing the death
of your ex-boyfriend last year.

21:36.890 --> 21:39.279
Okay, look,
i know this sounds crazy.

21:39.290 --> 21:41.884
That's why I didn't
come to you right away.
I was scared.

21:41.890 --> 21:43.426
I-i didn't know
how to explain this.

21:43.430 --> 21:46.558
But, after what happened
to Jake...

21:46.570 --> 21:49.095
You have to believe me.

21:50.640 --> 21:52.596
I believe you.

21:52.600 --> 21:57.867
I mean, I believe you believe
what you're saying to be true.

21:59.510 --> 22:02.047
So, that's it?
If what you're saying is true,

22:02.050 --> 22:05.213
you're the victim here,
you're not one of the bad guys.

22:05.220 --> 22:06.642
So, for now, that's it.

22:06.650 --> 22:10.541
Please take Emma back
to the learning center.

22:18.200 --> 22:19.497
(Sighs)

22:21.330 --> 22:23.594
With all due respect, sheriff,
letting her off so easy

22:23.600 --> 22:26.467
and looking the other way
when it comes to a gun
on campus?

22:26.470 --> 22:28.165
You ever hear
of Stockholm syndrome?

22:28.170 --> 22:29.637
Keep them bottled up
long enough,

22:29.640 --> 22:31.631
act like the nice guy
in a bad situation,

22:31.640 --> 22:35.098
and, inevitably,
they come to your side.

22:35.610 --> 22:37.339
Jake Fitzgerald...

22:37.350 --> 22:39.614
Had some bad habits,
made some pretty strong enemies.

22:39.620 --> 22:41.440
One of them wanted
to kill this kid.

22:41.450 --> 22:44.954
You think it could be
one of the lakewood six?
It's the lakewood five now.

22:44.960 --> 22:47.349
And, sure, even that sweet girl
that just walked out of here

22:47.360 --> 22:49.089
could be a sociopath,
for all we know.

22:49.090 --> 22:51.251
But I'm not gonna
narrow it down to five people.

22:51.260 --> 22:54.354
Whoever it was,
they're probably not finished.

23:02.670 --> 23:07.004
So... I found Jake Fitzgerald,
just like you asked.

23:07.010 --> 23:09.706
That is not even
remotely funny.

23:09.720 --> 23:12.348
My daughter is coming
home with me, now.

23:12.350 --> 23:16.116
I fully understand your concern,
but I still need to ask her
a few questions.

23:16.120 --> 23:17.519
Not without me present.

23:17.520 --> 23:20.978
She might be more honest
if you're not in the room.

23:20.990 --> 23:22.457
Am I a suspect, Miguel?

23:22.460 --> 23:25.588
No. You'd never drop a body
in front of your daughter.

23:25.600 --> 23:29.366
A freezer in the garage...
Now, that's more your style.

23:31.270 --> 23:32.999
He's a good guy
and a decent cop...

23:33.010 --> 23:35.035
Oh, my god. Whatever!
Okay, now, he thinks I'm crazy.

23:35.040 --> 23:38.259
He went straight to asking me
about PTSD and the psych ward.

23:38.280 --> 23:42.649
Look, in times like this,
you have to be careful
with who you trust.

23:42.650 --> 23:44.208
What?

23:44.220 --> 23:45.016
Hey!

23:45.020 --> 23:47.614
Whoa, we all need
to calm down. Hey!

23:49.190 --> 23:51.545
She had the dead guy's phone
and they just sent her back.

23:51.560 --> 23:54.313
Why? Because her mom
works for the police. Duh!

23:54.330 --> 23:56.548
Why are they all staring?
Ignore it.

23:56.560 --> 23:59.028
No, i-i want to know
what they have to say.

23:59.030 --> 24:01.624
She's not worth it.
Emma, just...
stop it!

24:03.140 --> 24:04.425
Hey.

24:05.540 --> 24:08.168
Do you have something
you want to say to me?

24:09.040 --> 24:11.133
Look, I know that you're scared.
We are all scared.

24:11.140 --> 24:15.406
But we should not be scared
of each other, okay?
Please do not be scared of me.

24:15.410 --> 24:18.413
But I am scared of you.
Everyone who comes
around you dies.

24:18.420 --> 24:22.481
And your friends
should be scared, too,
because they're all gonna die.

24:26.690 --> 24:28.248
You have no idea
what I went through.

24:28.260 --> 24:30.182
You went through?
Piper butchered eight people,

24:30.200 --> 24:32.054
but magically didn't touch
a hair on your head.

24:32.060 --> 24:34.051
That is not true.
Then, you shot her
in the face,

24:34.070 --> 24:36.368
so we only got
your side of the story.
Audrey: That's enough, Hayley.

24:36.370 --> 24:39.168
Leave her alone.
Her whole family is crazy,
aren't they?

24:39.170 --> 24:40.592
Anytime there's
a killer loose, somehow,

24:40.610 --> 24:43.408
there's always
a crazy duval left standing!

24:43.740 --> 24:46.402
(Students gasping)

24:57.920 --> 24:59.251
You dumb bitch!

24:59.260 --> 25:03.026
(Students yelling)

25:03.030 --> 25:05.055
Hey, get off her!

25:05.060 --> 25:06.425
Get off!

25:07.070 --> 25:11.291
Man: Hey, hey, break it up!
Woman: Break it up!
Leave her alone!

25:11.940 --> 25:13.589
Are you okay?

25:13.610 --> 25:17.205
Come on, let's get you
out of here. Come on.

25:17.210 --> 25:19.303
Get out of the way.
Get out of the way.

25:19.310 --> 25:21.949
Move. Out of the way.
Okay, guys, back it up.

25:21.950 --> 25:23.201
All right. Okay.
You okay?

25:23.220 --> 25:26.974
So, when was the last time
you saw Jake?

25:26.990 --> 25:28.685
Sunday night.

25:29.350 --> 25:31.318
Here at the pool.

25:33.060 --> 25:35.278
We snuck in to have sex.

25:35.630 --> 25:38.349
Okay, um, so...
(Chuckles)

25:38.360 --> 25:43.297
Trespassing. But I get it.
It's... it's fun, right? Right?

25:43.300 --> 25:47.532
Anything else you want
to tell me about that night?

25:47.540 --> 25:50.634
We had a fight.
About...?

25:52.040 --> 25:57.546
My father. He had
a problem with Jake.

25:58.220 --> 26:02.145
Jake wanted to go public
about us, but I...

26:04.590 --> 26:06.455
I chose my dad.

26:07.360 --> 26:10.022
Look, I know who did this.

26:11.160 --> 26:16.166
Seth Branson,
my former... teacher.

26:16.170 --> 26:20.595
He's been sending me texts,
flowers, showing up everywhere...

26:20.610 --> 26:25.138
Sweetheart, you never...
There is a restraining order.

26:25.140 --> 26:27.404
He was stalking you?

26:27.410 --> 26:29.002
We used to call it
something else,

26:29.010 --> 26:30.978
but, yeah,
he's been stalking me.

26:30.980 --> 26:32.538
And you think he's capable?

26:32.550 --> 26:34.211
Why would he do
something like this?

26:34.220 --> 26:37.348
I think he did this
because of me.

26:39.020 --> 26:41.159
I want to go see Jake.

26:44.000 --> 26:45.297
Alone.

26:49.500 --> 26:51.320
(Hyperventilating)

26:51.340 --> 26:54.138
I can't believe I hit her.
I've never done anything
like that before.

26:54.140 --> 26:58.429
Just breathe.
You're experiencing
multiple PTSD triggers:

26:58.440 --> 26:59.600
Grief, anxiety, fear...

26:59.610 --> 27:02.147
Heightening your
fight-or-flight response.

27:02.150 --> 27:03.606
Okay.

27:03.620 --> 27:06.316
I'm... I'm shaking.
That's the adrenaline.

27:06.320 --> 27:09.585
It's gonna take a second
to work through your body.
What you need to do is rest.

27:09.590 --> 27:13.549
Here. I'm gonna check back
at the learning center.

27:13.560 --> 27:16.279
Stay here. Relax.

27:16.290 --> 27:17.723
Okay.

27:17.730 --> 27:19.095
Ms. lang?

27:19.100 --> 27:21.728
I..._I don't want this
to drive me crazy again.

27:21.730 --> 27:24.597
Something terrible
just happened to somebody
that you cared about.

27:24.600 --> 27:28.331
It's bringing up
a lot of emotions.
That's not crazy, Emma.

27:28.340 --> 27:30.103
That's normal.

27:45.420 --> 27:47.456
(Breathing heavily)

27:51.230 --> 27:52.720
He's obsessed
with the lakewood six.

27:52.730 --> 27:55.494
He was the one handing out
the doped-up shots last night.

27:55.500 --> 27:57.388
He's drawing our friends
being brutally murdered.

27:57.400 --> 28:00.460
Now, hello,
one of our friends has
been brutally murdered!

28:00.470 --> 28:02.609
I'm telling you
it's not stavo, okay?

28:02.610 --> 28:05.135
He's one of us...
A horror fan, a friend.

28:05.140 --> 28:08.769
And if you're right
and I'm wrong,
i will apologize.

28:08.780 --> 28:11.544
But, if I'm right,
what are you gonna say

28:11.550 --> 28:13.541
when I'm the one
hanging from a banner

28:13.550 --> 28:16.348
with my insides
on the outside?

28:16.350 --> 28:18.409
(Scoffs)

28:22.760 --> 28:24.682
Dude, the emergency door
is disarmed.

28:24.700 --> 28:26.429
If you can sneak
into the service hallway,

28:26.430 --> 28:29.160
you can get back in
without being caught.

28:42.250 --> 28:43.569
(Sighs)

28:53.330 --> 28:55.890
He was really beautiful.

28:55.890 --> 28:57.528
You scared me.

28:59.630 --> 29:03.191
How long has he been
like this?

29:03.600 --> 29:05.261
I can't comment
on an open case

29:05.270 --> 29:06.897
and these are just
initial findings.

29:06.910 --> 29:10.209
Maggie! Please.

29:10.210 --> 29:11.802
I need to know.

29:13.550 --> 29:15.905
I'd say two or three days.

29:18.480 --> 29:20.710
It's impossible.

29:20.720 --> 29:23.883
No! He couldn't! He...

29:36.230 --> 29:38.767
(Metal scraping)

29:56.220 --> 29:58.950
(Phone ringing)

30:05.900 --> 30:08.892
(Suspenseful music playing)

30:11.800 --> 30:16.908
Hello?
Distorted voice:
He/io, Emma. Did you miss me?

30:16.910 --> 30:19.708
Well, I’m coming for you!

30:19.710 --> 30:21.803
(Suspenseful music playing)

30:28.520 --> 30:30.886
(Banging)

30:30.890 --> 30:34.519
(Metal scraping)

30:49.370 --> 30:52.430
(Grunts)
Not this time!

31:15.330 --> 31:19.460
I am not gonna play
your games anymore!

31:22.740 --> 31:28.474
I know you, Maggie.
You hide it well,
but you're an emotional person.

31:28.480 --> 31:30.471
This must be hard for you.

31:30.480 --> 31:31.947
I'm okay.

31:31.950 --> 31:34.669
I'm removing you
from this case.

31:35.750 --> 31:38.742
What?
I saw you reveal
privileged information

31:38.760 --> 31:40.489
that could compromise
this investigation.

31:40.490 --> 31:42.629
That was Brooke. The girl
just lost her boyfriend.

31:42.630 --> 31:47.294
You see that girl and you see
your daughter's friend.
You should see a suspect.

31:47.300 --> 31:50.895
That girl was, as far
as I can tell, the last person
to see the victim alive.

31:50.900 --> 31:52.595
They had an argument
alone in this building,

31:52.600 --> 31:55.933
and, a few days later,
his body drops from
a banner above her head.

31:55.940 --> 31:57.965
The girl is clearly
being victimized.

31:57.980 --> 32:01.575
And you're too close
to this by a mile.

32:01.580 --> 32:04.743
You're just gonna have
to sit this one out.

32:04.750 --> 32:06.718
Are you serious, Miguel?

32:07.390 --> 32:09.711
Dwayne'll get your notes
on the way out of the building.

32:09.720 --> 32:11.312
You're having me
escorted out?

32:11.320 --> 32:13.254
I'm sorry, Maggie.
I don't want to make you

32:13.260 --> 32:15.751
choose between being a mother
and a medical examiner.

32:15.760 --> 32:19.389
So, yeah, I'm having you
removed from the scene.

32:25.670 --> 32:27.228
(Sighs)

32:27.740 --> 32:29.298
(Sighs)

32:57.800 --> 33:01.338
Audrey!
Dude, you scared
the crap out of me!

33:01.340 --> 33:02.602
I'm sorry.

33:02.610 --> 33:04.737
You okay? I was out there
and you were in here

33:04.740 --> 33:07.709
and itjust...
it felt weird.
What do you mean?

33:07.710 --> 33:10.577
We're always together
in times of intense peril,

33:10.580 --> 33:13.913
and, I don't know,
H was worried about you.

33:13.920 --> 33:17.811
Oh. Thanks. Anyway,
I've been watching stavo.
Stavo? I'm telling you...

33:17.820 --> 33:20.983
And I'm telling you
this guy could be
seriously messed up, Noah.

33:20.990 --> 33:25.450
We barely know the kid.
I'm sorry he doesn't fit
your accomplice profile,

33:25.460 --> 33:27.997
but he's got the same
twisted sense of humor

33:28.000 --> 33:30.889
as the freak
that's been calling me.

33:30.900 --> 33:32.458
You've been getting calls?

33:32.470 --> 33:35.962
I'm talking about the texts,
the ones I showed you, the ones
i got when Emma got back.

33:35.970 --> 33:39.701
You said "calls."
Plus, didn't you think
they were just pranks?

33:39.710 --> 33:42.599
I meant texts, Noah,
and I don't know what they are.

33:42.610 --> 33:47.547
Whatever! Stavo basically
has "crazy psychopath"
tattooed on his forehead,

33:47.550 --> 33:49.086
and I'm supposed
to just ignore it?

33:49.090 --> 33:50.910
I can't. No, not under
these circumstances.

33:50.920 --> 33:53.354
People are dying.
People? It's just one so far.

33:53.360 --> 33:57.478
You're... you're my favorite
person in the world,
but you're acting weird.

33:57.500 --> 33:59.752
We're all freaking out
about Jake right now,
i get it,

33:59.760 --> 34:02.524
but, trust me, you really
need to take a breath.

34:02.530 --> 34:05.897
Piper was right under
our noses and nobody saw it.
Neither of us.

34:05.900 --> 34:09.631
So, what? You're just gonna
go over there and accuse him
of being a psycho killer?

34:09.640 --> 34:12.063
He's been sketching us,
Noah. All of us!

34:12.080 --> 34:15.743
Today, I saw him
drawing Kieran and Eli
in a pool of blood.

34:15.750 --> 34:17.968
Today, he was doing that!
Wow. Of all days.

34:17.980 --> 34:20.847
Yeah, I know!
It's... (Sighs)

34:20.850 --> 34:23.648
I'm just gonna ask him what
that's all about. That's it.

34:23.660 --> 34:25.981
It's not weird.
It'd be weird if we didn't.

34:25.990 --> 34:27.912
You, stavo!
What are you drawing?

34:27.930 --> 34:29.056
Don't worry about it.

34:29.060 --> 34:30.925
Come on, you're staring
at us all the time.

34:30.930 --> 34:32.921
I'd love to see
what we inspire in you.

34:32.930 --> 34:35.660
Hey! Give that back!
What the hell
is wrong with you?

34:35.670 --> 34:40.095
What is she doing?
She was just gonna ask him
what he was drawing.

34:40.810 --> 34:43.131
Give it back! It's not...
Look, it's not...

34:43.140 --> 34:46.576
What is it not?
You want me to show everybody
what you think it's not?

34:46.580 --> 34:50.072
(Students murmuring)
This is what he's drawing!

34:50.080 --> 34:51.399
Oh, my god. You sicko!

34:51.420 --> 34:53.149
They're just drawings!
So, just give it back...

34:53.150 --> 34:58.144
(students murmuring)
You know what? It looks
like it's more! A lot more!

34:58.160 --> 35:00.048
It's not what you think!
It's not what you think!

35:00.060 --> 35:01.812
You know who does that?
Serial killers!

35:01.830 --> 35:05.550
_A||: Yeah! _
Wait, wait, wait!
Wait a minute! Wait a minute!

35:05.560 --> 35:09.929
Boy: That's messed up, man!
(All gasping, murmuring)

35:09.930 --> 35:14.492
Boy: That's gross!
It's just... it's just
a comic book, all right?

35:14.510 --> 35:16.102
It's a fantasy.
It's not real life.

35:16.110 --> 35:19.170
Liar!
No, no, no!
Careful with that!

35:19.180 --> 35:20.636
(Students gasping)

35:20.650 --> 35:22.845
Girl:
That is not all right!

35:24.920 --> 35:28.014
(Students shouting, cheering)

35:35.130 --> 35:38.657
Sheriff, we've got
a big situation!

35:38.660 --> 35:40.059
(All yelling)

35:40.060 --> 35:42.051
What did you do?

35:42.070 --> 35:45.096
What is wrong
with you all? Get back!

35:45.640 --> 35:47.596
Break it up! Break it up!

35:47.610 --> 35:51.899
Break it up! Break up!
Back off! Back off!

36:04.620 --> 36:05.484
Emma?

36:05.490 --> 36:09.017
(Suspenseful music playing)

36:32.880 --> 36:36.782
Woma n :
throw me down

36:36.790 --> 36:39.554
I’ll steal the moon

36:39.990 --> 36:41.855
I’ll tear the night . .

36:41.860 --> 36:43.987
Emma, we know how hard
this day has been,

36:44.000 --> 36:46.821
and the sheriff and i
are a little concerned

36:46.830 --> 36:48.525
about your emotional
and mental state.

36:48.530 --> 36:52.830
I appreciate that.
You want to tell us
what happened?

36:54.510 --> 36:55.738
I had a panic attack.

36:55.740 --> 36:58.208
Panic? You threw a chair
through a window.

36:58.210 --> 37:01.577
Well, when I realized
that I was locked in that room,

37:01.580 --> 37:03.070
I just... I lost it.

37:03.080 --> 37:07.039
The adrenaline
must've heightened
my fight-or-flight response.

37:07.050 --> 37:08.039
Right, Ms. lang?

37:08.050 --> 37:09.813
I just wanted
to make sure she was safe.

37:09.820 --> 37:12.709
Oh, of course.
You probably should
have stayed with her.

37:12.720 --> 37:16.656
Anything else
you want to tell us
about what happened, Emma?

37:18.530 --> 37:20.828
No, sheriff, that's it.

37:21.630 --> 37:23.894
Okay. You're free to go.

37:30.210 --> 37:33.202
Hey! You okay?

37:33.210 --> 37:35.178
Yeah, I'm fine.

37:36.050 --> 37:37.699
I'm sorry.

37:42.520 --> 37:44.841
I'm sorry I...
I told him about the phone.

37:44.860 --> 37:48.910
Uh, yeah, I guess you thought
that was the best way
to handle it?

37:48.930 --> 37:52.024
But Audrey's right.
Someone's messing with us,
and our choices matter,

37:52.030 --> 37:56.763
and I would like to think
that you trust me enough
to make my own.

37:56.770 --> 37:58.522
Of course I do.

38:00.300 --> 38:02.234
Can I take you home?

38:03.140 --> 38:07.702
No, I thinkI need to be
alone for a little bit,
if that's okay.

38:07.710 --> 38:10.304
Are you the one for me?

38:10.310 --> 38:14.110
time Is wasted and...

38:14.120 --> 38:18.238
I’m not losing sleep

38:18.260 --> 38:21.718
don ’t just stand and stare

38:21.730 --> 38:25.188
come on
and bare your teeth

38:25.200 --> 38:28.590
I could take you there

38:28.600 --> 38:32.866
if you let me see

